There are several ways to create a new ICal.timetype:

  • ICal.icaltime_null_time()

    • ICal.icaltime_null_date()

    • ICal.icaltime_current_time_with_zone()

    • ICal.icaltime_today()

    • ICal.icaltime_from_timet_with_zone(time_t tm, int is_date, ICal.timezone *zone)

    • ICal.icaltime_from_day_of_year(int doy, int year)

      italtimetype objects can be converted to different formats:

    • ICal.icaltime_as_timet(struct ICal.timetype tt)

    • ICal.icaltime_as_timet_with_zone(struct ICal.timetype tt, ICal.timezone *zone)

    • ICal.icaltime_as_ical_string(struct ICal.timetype tt)

      Accessor methods include:

    • ICal.icaltime_get_timezone(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_get_tzid(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_set_timezone(struct ICal.timetype t, const ICal.timezone *zone)

    • ICal.icaltime_day_of_year(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_day_of_week(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_start_doy_week(struct ICal.timetype t, int fdow)

    • ICal.icaltime_week_number(struct ICal.timetype t)

      Query methods include:

    • ICal.icaltime_is_null_time(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_is_valid_time(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_is_date(struct ICal.timetype t)

    • ICal.icaltime_is_utc(struct ICal.timetype t)

      Modify, compare and utility methods include:

    • ICal.icaltime_compare(struct ICal.timetype a,struct ICal.timetype b)

    • ICal.icaltime_compare_date_only(struct ICal.timetype a, struct ICal.timetype b)

    • ICal.icaltime_adjust(struct ICal.timetype *tt, int days, int hours, int minutes, int seconds);

    • ICal.icaltime_normalize(struct ICal.timetype t);

    • ICal.icaltime_convert_to_zone(const struct ICal.timetype tt, ICal.timezone *zone);
